fields.title: Getting Started with Django REST Framework
fields.content: Django REST Framework is a powerful toolkit for building Web APIs in Django. It provides a lot of built-in functionality including serialization, authentication, permissions, and much more. In this blog post, we'll explore the basics of setting up a simple API.

fields.title: JWT Authentication in Modern Web Applications
fields.content: JSON Web Tokens (JWT) have become a popular choice for handling authentication in modern web applications. They provide a stateless way to manage user sessions and can be easily used across different services and platforms. This post covers the implementation of JWT authentication in a Django REST API.
